---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contact Me" description="Kevin W. Griffin | Developer, Training, Entrepreneur">
  <div class="py-16 mx-auto container-inner">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold leading-tight">Contact Me</h1>

    <p class="pb-3">
      I know how it goes. You're cruising around the internet, find this
      awesome dude Kevin, and you want to reach out to him... err, me.
    </p>
    <p class="pb-3">There are a couple ways:</p>

    <h2 class="pt-6 text-2xl font-bold">Twitter</h2>
    <p>
      One of the quickest ways to reach out is to send me a direct message on
      Twitter. I can be contacted at
      <a href="https://twitter.com/1kevgriff" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">@1kevgriff</a>.
    </p>
    <h2 class="pt-6 text-2xl font-bold">Email</h2>
    <p>
      A solid fallback is to
      <a href="mailto:connect@consultwithgriff.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">email</a> me.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
